name: Mie Lontong Tahu Badrun (Street Food)
address: Jl. Turi No.21, Kesiman, Kec. Denpasar Tim., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80235, Indonesia
review 1:
This the place to enjoy a bowl of unique noodle. But be advise.. no table available..
You are eating sitting on sidewalk.
But not bad.. im still enjoying..
Noodles very tasty and filling..
Come at night, place is sometimes crowded.. sometimes no one there to buy.
Don't come when raining unless you are have no problem eating under the rain.
review 2: Great street food with cheap price, unique taste because there is noodle, vegetables, tempe, tofu, top with peanut sauce !! Recommended!! But the place little bit dark. I don't mind with it
review 3: Very delicious noodle shop, not recommended if you hate sweet soy sauce or you haven't try any kind of peanut sauce.
review 4: This place was worth to visit,, they have a delicious traditional food with a clean area, friendly services and one important thing is that you don't have to wait for a long time to enjoy your food  and of course with low price.üëçüëç
review 5: Simple menus : instant noodle and tofu with peanut sauce, yet very famous among youngster

name: Daerah tujuan wisata tukad bindu
address: Jl. Turi, Kesiman, Kec. Denpasar Tim., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80235, Indonesia
review 1: Me and my son had the best time in here. Beautiful and kind people, good to hang around local area. It‚Äôs not touristic place, but also you can meet warm Balinese people. Nice chilling and relax vibes. Highly recommend.
review 2: Very local!. Quite clean, green, offers a lot of Balinese cuisine options. There is "Peken Nusantara" or Nusantara Market with Balinese style food stalls, local foods and snacks even small coffee shop. Affordable and reasonable price for the foods & beverages. No entry fee, only pay for parking (motorbike). If you bring a car, you need to find the parking outside by the main street.
review 3:
Tukad Bindu is one of the leasure and comfort place to visit in Denpasar City
Surrounded by the hectic life of capital city, this place offer the visitors to have a less noisy sound of the city
Visitor can relax and have a sight seeing in the Jati Forest, where it has a coworking space next to the river and also a small vegetable garden managed by the villahe woman community, and also catfish aquaculture
A riverside walk from Tukad Bindu also invite the visitor to enjoy the little natural greens and look some of the rest of the Dutch construction with the Oongan Dam located on the other side
At the time I write this, unfortunately it does not have many toilets and some available are not very representatives to be visit by foreigners in general
review 4:
Good place to visit in Denpasar Bali. you can enjoy the atmosphere in the morning and do workout at here

you will get a fresh air too, dont forget to bring your kids because in here available a kids playground.

there is a food corner and coffee corner
review 5: Nice little park in the heart of denpasar. The river is so clean, nice option to enjoy river sidewalk with family.

review 1: Good taste, good portion, open air tables available but limited parking area. No satay or soup in the normal portion.
review 2: One of my favorite ‚Äúhidden gem‚Äù babi guling in Bali. Must try when visit bali!
review 3: fairly low price and pretty tasty, one serving is perfect for your breakfast
review 4: Its yummie, with crispy pork and rice , my breakfast menu every sunday

Pelayanan pada peak hour sudah tidak sebagus dulu. Pelanggan take-out dibiarkan mengantri berpanas-panasan sambil menunggu nasinya matang.
It still tastes the same, with the same price. But the service quality fell compared to the past.

‚Äîedit:
I wrote bad review about a year ago, but nowadays the quality has improved to acceptable level. I must say I'm impressed, and I hope at least they can maintain the same level of taste and service in the future.

name: Tri Pawns Kopi
address: Jl. WR Supratman No.137, Sumerta, Kec. Denpasar Tim., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80235, Indonesia
review 1: Good place to go, i like their pandan coffee taste good and very affordable! Mie nyemek and kaya toast just ok. Nice place to day dreaming lol
review 2: Tri Pawns Kopi is not your typical cafe. Its simplistic charm and limited menu options evoke a sense of nostalgia, reminding me of the carefree days of my youth. Situated alongside a bustling river in Denpasar, this little gem offers a serene escape where one can unwind and enjoy the picturesque riverside view. As much as I appreciate the caf√©'s ambiance, I can't help but wish that the owner would consider adding some beer to their menu for those moments when I want to gather my fellow dads for a good chat over drinks.
review 3: good place, good taste, and very good price. Really recommend mie nyemek and kopi pandan.
